<reference id="rrefsqlj16221" xml:lang="en-us">
<title>SMALLINT data type</title>
<prolog><metadata>
<keywords><indexterm>SMALLINT data type</indexterm></keywords>
</metadata></prolog>
<refbody>
<section> <p>SMALLINT provides 2 bytes of storage.</p></section>
<refsyn><title>Syntax</title> <codeblock><b>SMALLINT</b></codeblock> </refsyn>
<section><title>Corresponding compile-time Java type</title> <p><i>java.lang.Short</i></p> </section>
<section><title>JDBC metadata type (java.sql.Types)</title> <p>SMALLINT</p> </section>
<section><title>Minimum value</title> <p id="sqlj22378">-32768 (<i>java.lang.Short.MIN_VALUE</i>)</p> </section>
<section><title>Maximum value</title> <p id="sqlj97879">32767
(<i>java.lang.Short.MAX_VALUE</i>)</p> <p>When mixed with other data types
in expressions, the resulting data type follows the rules shown in <xref href="rrefsqlj27767.dita#rrefsqlj27767"></xref>.</p> <p>See
also <xref href="rrefsqlj20204.dita#rrefsqlj20204"></xref>.</p> <p>Constants in the
appropriate format always map to INTEGER or BIGINT, depending on their length.</p> </section>
</refbody>
